activities:
Time Warner Inc. may collect and use personal data from its past, present and prospective employees, their beneficiaries, dependents and emergency contacts, contractors, consultants, vendors, and other individuals who provide services to Time Warner Inc. and/or to any of its affiliated or subsidiary companies.  Purposes for which Time Warner Inc. may collect and use personal data include the following (the databases and/or systems where the data resides are noted in parentheses, all of which are managed and hosted by Time Warner Inc. except where noted with an asterisk, which are independently owned and managed by a third-party):

•	Human resources functions, including training, career and succession planning, administering employee contracts, diversity initiatives, employee evaluations, implementing employee-related actions and obligations and providing employment benefits and related information (Business Objects Reporting, Business Standards & Practices; Compensation Planning; NYSE Governance Services (formerly Corpedia); Diversity Administration; Employee Connection; FitNation; HRIS Administration; Human Resources Data Central and Reporting; Manager Toolkit; Peoplesoft; Personnel Action Form; SharePoint; Stock Plan Data Central; UK Databases; Virgin Pulse);
•	Human capital management (Enterprise Data Warehouse; My Contacts; Talent View; );
•	Recruitment and hiring activities (Brass Ring*; Encore);
•	Business continuity and disaster recovery (SunGard Business Continuity Planning);
•	Tracking and reporting ethics and compliance incidents (Ethics Incident Tracking System; Navex Global (formerly, EthicsPoint*);
•	Tracking and reporting conflicts of interest (Annual Conflicts of Interest Questionnaire);
•	Expense and travel management (Concur; PFM; PFM Wireless);
•	Document Management (iManage);
•	Legal (Oneworld Legal; Lawweb Phone Directory; WebTMS);
•	Risk Management (Claimstracking);
•	Budgeting (LongView 7-LVAct);
•	Electronic Communication (Airwatch*; Good; Keystone; Outlook; People Directory);
•	Mail and package shipment and reporting (DX; SendSuite Live; SendSuite Shipping and Tracking; ShipMatrix) and
•	Incident Management and Solutions (D3 Incident Management System; Remedy)
